@SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress = http://localhost:5027

### Get all orders
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders

### Get order by id
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/1

### Get the same order by using an alternate URL
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/details/1

### Get the same order by using another alternate URL
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/order-details/1

### Get orders by customer name
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/customer/Asha

### Get orders by status
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/status/Preparing

### Get orders by customer and status using route parameters
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/customer/Asha/status/Placed

### Search orders by area
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/search?area=RS%20Puram

### Advanced search using multiple query string values
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/advanced-search?restaurantName=Annapoorna&deliveryArea=Gandhipuram&status=Placed&minAmount=200&maxAmount=300

### Get paged orders using query string values
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/paged?pageNumber=1&pageSize=2

### Track order by id
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/1/track

### Track the same order by using an alternate URL
GET {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/track-order/1

### Create a new order
POST {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customerName": "Karthik",
  "restaurantName": "Pizza Plaza",
  "deliveryArea": "Peelamedu",
  "status": "Placed",
  "totalAmount": 410
}

### Update order status
PUT {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/1/status/Delivered

### Delete an order
DELETE {{SwiggyRelated.API_HostAddress}}/api/orders/3
